 Thousands of Catalans have gathered to protest against the board over Messi’s decision to leave Barcelona. The legendary player reportedly informed Barcelona of his decision to leave the club he has been part of for over two decades, sparking frenzy globally. The Argentinian wants to part with the club of his childhood because of dissatisfaction with the board headed by Josep Bartomeu. People gather near Camp Nou and the club’s offices to protest against the board and Leo Messi’s exit. Barca’s CEO Oscar Grau is leaving the club’s offices, the fans aren’t hesitating to show their frustration with the latest turn of events. Some of the concerned people are shouting ‘Bartomeu, resign!’